{{Infobox person | name = Arundell Esdaile | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = Arundell James Kennedy Esdaile | birth_date = 1880 | birth_place = | death_date = 22 June 1956 | death_place = | death_cause = | nationality = British | residence = | education = | alma mater = | occupation = Librarian | title = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | known for = Secretary to the [[British Museum]], 1926-40 | boards = | salary = | networth = | spouse = [[Katharine Esdaile|Katharine Ada McDowall]] | children = 3 | parents = | relations = [[Ada Benson]] (mother-in-law) | website = }}
'''Arundell James Kennedy Esdaile''' {{post-nominals|country=GBR|CBE}} (1880 - 22 June 1956), was a British librarian, and Secretary to the [[British Museum]] from 1926 to 1940.
==Career== Esdaile was Secretary to the [[British Museum]] from 1926 to 1940.<ref name="ODNB">{{cite web|last1=Baker|first1=Malcolm |title=Esdaile [née McDowall], Katharine Ada|url=http://www.oxforddnb.com/view/10.1093/ref:odnb/9780198614128.001.0001/odnb-9780198614128-e-33026|website=ODNB|accessdate=30 November 2017}}</ref><ref name="auto">{{cite journal|url=https://doi.org/10.1177/096100068001200402|title=Arundell Esdaile : a centenary tribute|first=James G.|last=Ollé|date=1 October 1980|publisher=|journal=Journal of librarianship|volume=12|issue=4|pages=217–228|accessdate=2 December 2017|via=SAGE Journals|doi=10.1177/096100068001200402}}</ref>
He was president of the [[Chartered Institute of Library and Information Professionals|Library Association]], and editor of its journal, the ''[[Library Association Record]]''.<ref name="auto"/>
He was appointed a CBE.<ref name="auto1">{{cite journal|last1=G. B.|first1=|last2=B.|first2=G.|date=1 October 1956|title=ARUNDELL JAMES KENNEDY ESDAILE, C.B.E., Litt.D. 1880-1956|url=https://academic.oup.com/english/article-abstract/11/63/96/390898|journal=English|volume=11|issue=63|pages=96–96|doi=10.1093/english/11.63.96|accessdate=2 December 2017|via=Oxford Academic}}</ref>
==Personal life== In 1907, he married the art historian [[Katharine Esdaile|Katharine Ada McDowall]], and they had a daughter followed by two sons.<ref name="ODNB"/>
==Later life== Esdaile died on 22 June 1956.<ref name="auto1"/>
