{{Infobox park |name = National Herbarium |photo = Qaumi Botigarh Islamabad.JPG |photo size = |alt = |photo_caption = |map = |map caption = |type = [[Herbarium]] |location = [[Islamabad]], [[Pakistan]] |coords = |area = |plants = |species = |collections = ~100,000 |opened = 1975 |owner = |operator = |budget = |visitation_num= |status = |website = }}
The '''National Herbarium''' is an [[herbarium]], located in [[Islamabad]], [[Pakistan]].
==History and collection== The largest herbarium in Pakistan, it was established in 1975 with Dr. [[Ralph Randles Stewart]]'s collection as its initial beginning. It has a collection of over 100,000 plants. The plants in the herbarium are divided into [[magnoliophyte]]s ([[dicotyledon]]s and [[monocotyledon]]s), [[gymnosperm]]s and [[Pteridophyta|pteridophytes]] (or ferns) and they are placed according to families, genera; and species arranged in alphabetical order.
==See also== * [[List of botanical gardens in Pakistan]] * [[List of herbaria]] {{clear}}
